In a #bowl{}, mix @Oil{1%tbsp} with half the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{2%sachets}.
Add the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%grams} to the bowl.
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
Toss to coat in the spices and set aside.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

== Pickled Onion ==

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).
Pop the onion into a bowl along with @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, @Salt{1/4%tsp} and the
@Red Wine Vinegar{1%sachet}. Set aside, continuing to stir at regular intervals.

== Chicken and Beans ==

Drain the @Black Beans{1%pack} in the #sieve{}.
Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.
Once hot, fry the chicken until cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.
When the chicken has cooked for ~{5%mins}, add the black beans and remaining Mexican spice.
Cook for the remaining time, ~{3-5%mins}.
> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Salad ==

Meanwhile, drain the @Sweetcorn{1%pack} in a sieve.
Chop the @Tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.
Trim the @Salad Leaves{120%grams} and roughly chop.
Roughly chop the @Coriander{5%grams}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).
In a #salad bowl{}, combine the corn, tomato, coriander, salad leaves and a
drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @Pepper{to taste}.

Quarter the @Lime{1}. In a #small bowl{}, mix the @Creme Fraiche{110%grams} with a
drizzle of oil and the juice of one lime wedge.

== To Serve ==

Divide the salad between plates. Spoon the beans with the chicken on top.
Drizzle over the creme fraiche dressing and garnish with the drained pickled onion.
Serve with the remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.